			<div class="content" id="post-content-2067542">
									

<p>I had no idea this was even a GOI. Still, its exciting.</p>
<p>I was interested who the photo was in real life, and it is apparently Arthur Bell, who lived near where I live, but in the 1900s. Breaking into houses in Newcastle is arguably less exciting than being a magic bootlegger in Chicago. (<a href="http://www.vintag.es/2012/08/mugshots-of-newcastle-upon-tyne.html">http://www.vintag.es/2012/08/mugshots-of-newcastle-upon-tyne.html</a>)</p>

